files.file_summary: A module providing utility functions for cluster maintenance and operations in DolphinDB.
This module handles alert generation and email notifications for log analysis results in DolphinDB.
Provides configuration management and environment setup for the DolphinDB log analyzer, including validation, initialization, and cleanup functions.
This file contains functions to parse and extract transaction-related information from DolphinDB log entries.
A DolphinDB script for parsing and analyzing log files, including functions for log line parsing, database table creation, and log processing handlers.
Main script for DolphinDB log analysis, handling both batch and streaming modes with configurable processing and reporting.
Provides utility functions for log analysis in DolphinDB, including querying log data by time range or limit, filtering by log level, and managing configuration.
Provides functionality for reading and parsing DolphinDB log files in both batch and streaming modes.
This script provides functionality to initialize and execute report generation processes for log analysis.
This script provides functions to parse and extract transaction-related information from various types of DolphinDB log entries.
Initializes the NSQ environment and sets up subscriptions for market data topics (orders, trade, snapshot) from specified exchanges (sh, sz).
Generates various transaction reports from log data including rolled back transactions, longest transactions, audit logs, metrics, and node-specific transaction details.
The module facilitates automatic loading of trading data from DataYes into DolphinDB databases with various configuration options.
Provides functions for creating and managing databases for different types of financial data.
Provides functionality to create and manage tables in DolphinDB databases for different market data types (snapshot, entrust, trade) with configurable market and time handling.
This module provides functions for loading and processing trading data from CSV files into DolphinDB databases, with support for date filtering and market-specific handling.
A module for subscribing to and managing NSQ real-time market data (orders, trades, snapshots) with options for stream and DFS table storage.
This module provides functions for transforming and loading entrust (order) data from Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchanges into a standardized format in DolphinDB.
Provides functions to load one day's worth of trading data for Shanghai and Shenzhen markets from CSV files into specified databases and tables.
This module provides functions to transform and load Shanghai market trade and entrust data from CSV files into DolphinDB tables, with options for merging, duplicate handling, and time concatenation.
Defines table schemas for entrust CSV data in Shenzhen and Shanghai markets.
This module provides functions to transform and load trade data from Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchanges into a standardized format in DolphinDB.
Defines schema structures for snapshot CSV data from Shenzhen and Shanghai stock markets based on trading dates.
This module provides functions to transform and load one day's worth of stock market snapshot and order queue data for Shanghai and Shenzhen markets into a standardized format in DolphinDB.
Defines the schema for order queue CSV data with specific column names and data types.
Defines the schema for trade and entrust CSV data for the Shanghai market.
Defines table schemas for trade CSV data in Shenzhen and Shanghai markets based on trading day.
Defines table schemas for trade data in Shenzhen and Shanghai markets, with options to concatenate or separate date and time fields.
Defines table schemas for snapshot data of Shenzhen and Shanghai markets with options for time format.
Defines table schemas for entrust data in Shenzhen and Shanghai markets with options for time format.
